Investors Should ‘Overweight’ Bonds, Raise Cash Levels, DBS Says

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-09-26T02:49:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/investors-should-overweight-bonds-raise-cash-levels-dbs-says.html
Investors should be “overweight”
in bonds and boost their cash holdings, according to  DBS Group
Holdings Ltd. (DBS)   While equities may stage a rebound in the near term, gains
won’t be sustainable amid the weakness in global economies, Lim
Say Boon, the chief investment officer of DBS, told reporters in
 Singapore .  To contact the reporter on this story:
